{# Port-wiring snippet for Node / Fastify backends.

Renders a port type-import + adapter wiring block intended for the
``FORGE:MIDDLEWARE_IMPORTS`` anchor in ``src/app.ts`` — the same
anchor queue_port + queue_bullmq already wire to. NestJS-style DI
container registration is a one-line variant on top: the spec
author supplies the registration through ``service_factory``
(``container.bind(QueuePort).to(BullmqAdapter)`` or
``app.register(<plugin>)``), and this macro emits the imports +
wiring around it.

Spec context (``port``) — every field is required:
  - name              — camelCase identifier (e.g. ``llm``, ``queue``)
  - interface_path    — module path of the Port interface; the macro
                        strips a trailing ``.ts`` / ``.py`` extension
                        and replaces it with the ``.js`` ESM suffix
                        (``app/ports/llm.ts`` → ``./app/ports/llm.js``).
                        Leading ``./`` is added when missing.
  - adapter_imports   — tuple of ``"<Symbol> from <module-path>"``
                        strings. Each becomes one
                        ``import { Symbol } from "<module>.js"`` line.
                        Bare module paths (no ``from``) become
                        side-effect imports (``import "<module>.js"``).
  - service_factory   — the wiring statement(s). Verbatim. Typically
                        an instantiation like
                        ``const _<port>Adapter: <Port> = new <Adapter>()``
                        or a NestJS ``container.register({...})`` call.
                        Multiline OK; the macro preserves indentation.
#}
{%- macro snippet(port) -%}
// Port: {{ port.name }}
{%- set _path = port.interface_path
    | replace('.ts', '')
    | replace('.py', '') -%}
{%- set _import_path = ('./' + _path) if not _path.startswith('.') else _path %}
import type * as {{ port.name }}Port from "{{ _import_path }}.js";
{% for imp in port.adapter_imports -%}
{% if ' from ' in imp -%}
{%- set _sym, _mod = imp.split(' from ', 1) -%}
import { {{ _sym }} } from "{{ _mod }}.js";
{%- else -%}
import "{{ imp }}.js";
{%- endif %}
{% endfor -%}
{{ port.service_factory }}
{%- endmacro %}
